article.headline: Southern Utah 83, IUPUI 62
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Nate Janes scored a career-high 25 points, and Henry Uhegwu added 17 points as Southern Utah beat IUPUI 83-62 in the regular-season finale for both teams Saturday night. Janes went 10-for-12 from the field and 5-for-5 from the foul line, while brother Rand Janes went 5-for-7 from the floor to finish with 14 points. The Thunderbirds (10-19, 8-8 Mid-Continent) shot 57 percent from the field and 53 percent from 3-point range. Southern Utah also made 16 of 17 free throws. George Hill led IUPUI (18-9, 13-3) with 21 points. The loss was the Jaguars' second straight after a nine-game win streak. Leading 40-37 less than a minute into the second half, the Thunderbirds scored 17 straight points. Rand Janes hit three 3-pointers during that stretch, and Nate Janes' layup with 13:53 left gave Southern Utah a 57-37 lead. By the time Hill hit a 3-pointer with 13:16 remaining, the Jaguars had gone 6:07 without scoring. Uhegwu responded with two free throws and Nate Janes added two more layups for a 21-point advantage. The closest IUPUI came after that was 18 points. With the loss, IUPUI fell into a tie with Oral Roberts for first place in the Mid-Continent Conference. Southern Utah wrapped up the fifth seed.
